# =====================================================================
# .env.example  —  a template for secrets (you do NOT need this yet)
# =====================================================================
# This file is intentionally EMPTY of real values and is safe to commit.
#
# A plain portfolio (this template) needs NO secrets at all — it's just
# static files. You only need a file like this if you grow into dynamic
# features later (a contact-form backend, a CMS, an API key, etc.).
#
# HOW IT WORKS, when the day comes:
#   1. Copy this file to a new file named exactly  .env
#   2. Put your real values in  .env  (the .gitignore keeps it private)
#   3. NEVER commit .env, and NEVER put secrets in config.js or any file
#      that ships to the browser — anyone can read those.
#
# See GROWING.md → "Sensitive info & secrets" for the full explanation.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------

# Example placeholders (these are NOT used by the static template):
# CONTACT_FORM_ENDPOINT=
# CMS_API_TOKEN=
# ANALYTICS_ID=
